<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4471928>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 3. Lower part of left cheek in ventrolateral view showing serrations on interopercle (IOP), preopercle (POP) and subopercle (SOP) in: A) Plectranthias longimanus, WAM P.28534-021, 22.8 mm SL (note that mouth is open); B) P. nanus, WAM P.28541-039, 24.3 mm SL. Dotted line shows junction between interopercle and subopercle; arrows indicate antrorse serrations on preopercle; scale bars = 2 mm. Illustrations by A.C. Gill." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4471928/files/figure.png" .

